original: Bramstång, Nils Torsten Valter, rådman, Varberg, f. 24/6/02 i Varberg av stat:skriv. Carl B. o. Ellen Rohlin. G. 31 m. ELsa Nelson. Barn: Gunnar f. 32, Mats Göran 36, Eva Agneta 38, Lilianne 43. — Stud:ex. i Halmstad 20, stud. i Lund 20, jur. kand. 25. E. o. not. i Svea hovr. 25, tingstjg. i Gällivare 25-28, andre rådman i Varberg 30, förste rådman o. not. publ. där sed. 44. Sekr. h. hälsov:ndn i Varberg sed. 33, omb :man i Varbergs Stads Sparbank sed. 44.
translated: Bramstång, Nils Torsten Valter, councilman, Varberg, b. 24/6/02 in Varberg to civil servant Carl B. and Ellen Rohlin. Married in 1931 to Elsa Nelson. Children: Gunnar b. 1932, Mats Göran b. 1936, Eva Agneta b. 1938, Lilianne b. 1943. He passed his studentexamen in Halmstad in 1920, studied in Lund in 1920, and qualified in law in 1925. He worked as a clerk in the Svea Court of Appeal in 1925, as a court clerk in Gällivare from 1925 to 1928, second councilman in Varberg in 1930, and first councilman and notary public there since 1944. Secretary for the Varberg Health Committee since 1933 and trustee for the Varberg City Savings Bank since 1944.
